achievements.title: MAINTAINING INSTITUTIONAL ATTENDANCE POLICY
achievements.description: Maintained attendance in accordance with institutional policy by achieving over 90%. This demonstrates my punctuality, perseverance, and sense of responsibility as a medical student.

achievements.title: EARLY CLINICAL EXPOSURE
achievements.description: Had the opportunity to engage in early clinical exposure by communicating with patients in the hospital and learning fundamental skills including measuring blood pressure and interpreting basic X rays,blood test reports.

achievements.title: GLOBAL FATTY LIVER WEBINAR
achievements.description: Received a certificate of participation for attending the Global Fatty Liver Webinar, where our Honorable Vice Chancellor delivered an insightful session. The session provided valuable insights into recent advances and global perspectives on fatty liver disease. It enriched my academic exposure and broadened my understanding of hepatology.

achievements.title: SUMMER INTERNSHIP PROGRAM BY MAS
achievements.description: Successfully completed the Online Summer Internship Program organized by the Medicos Aid Society and received a certificate of participation. The program included tasks such as preparing a medical first aid box, tree plantation, arranging water for laborers, and feeding stray animals, which fostered a sense of social responsibility, empathy, and teamwork.

achievements.title: BASIC INTERPRETATION OF X-RAY
achievements.description: "Gained experience in correlating theoretical anatomy with radiological images by interpreting basic bone X-rays in small group discussions. This strengthened my foundation in applied anatomy and improved clinical reasoning."

achievements.title: ACADEMIC PERFORMANCE-BLOCK ASSESSMENTS
achievements.description: Secured 81% in Block 1 and 82% in Block 2, reflecting steady academic performance and consistent effort. These results encourage me to keep striving for further improvement

reflections.title: BRUSHSTROKES OF HEALING
reflections.content: Received a certificate for participating in the Brushstrokes of Healing project organized by the Synch Society Arts Club. As someone passionate about art, this creative session allowed me to explore painting as a medium of self-expression and emotional well-being

reflections.title: DISSECTION OF HEART
reflections.content: Actively participated in the dissection of the heart during Anatomy small group discussions. This hands-on experience enhanced my understanding of cardiac anatomy, helped me visualize internal structures, and deepened my appreciation for the clinical relevance of gross anatomy."

personalInfo.title: Saman Zahra's Medfolio
personalInfo.bio: Passionate medical student dedicated 1. To impart evidence based research oriented medical education. 2. To provide best possible patient care. 3. To inculcate the values of mutual respect and ethical practice of medicine.
